Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Metanoia=‘Duo Sunt in Homine’
By: Paracelsus
---
Man has two spirits, a divine and an animal spirit. The former is from
the breath of God： the latter from the elements of the air and the
fire. He ought to live according to the life of the divine spirit and
not according to that of the animal.
